      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Clean, honest project-ready driver with strong mechanical character and plenty of life left in the chassis. Starts up, runs, and delivers the kind of analog road feel enthusiasts appreciate, with a powertrain that feels eager and well-sorted for a budget-friendly setup. Not a showpiece, but a usable car with good bones, straightforward serviceability, and solid potential as a dependable commuter, weekend tinkering platform, or entry-level enthusiast build. If you want something affordable that still feels capable and rewarding behind the wheel, this one is worth a look.",
      "price": 5950.0,
